Gleasonia is a genus of plants in the [[Rubiaceae]].<ref>Paul Carpenter Standley. 1931. Publications of the Field Columbian Museum. Botanical series 7: 372</ref> There are at the present time (May 2014) five accepted species, all native to [[South America]].<ref>[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=90026 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families]</ref>

*''[[Gleasonia cururuensis]]'' <small>Egler</small> - [[Brazil]]
*''[[Gleasonia duidana]]'' <small>Standl.</small> - [[Brazil]], [[Venezuela]], [[Guyana]]
**''Gleasonia duidana'' var. ''duidana'' - [[Brazil]], [[Venezuela]]
**''Gleasonia duidana'' var. ''latifolia'' <small>Steyerm.</small> - [[Brazil]], [[Venezuela]], [[Guyana]]
*''[[Gleasonia macrocalyx]]'' <small>Ducke</small> - [[Brazil]]
*''[[Gleasonia prancei]]'' <small>B.M.Boom</small>  - [[Brazil]]
*''[[Gleasonia uaupensis]]'' <small>Ducke</small>  - [[Brazil]]

